Jane-ChrisBScotland wrote a review Jan 2019
Dunfermline, United Kingdom35 contributions39 helpful votes
Good place to stay
Our daughter was living in da nang and we were going out to see her. Our daughter arranged a rate at the hotel which was not honoured by the booking centre. Given its proximity to our daughter we eventually paid the higher amount quoted by the booking centre. We had other friends joining us from Australia so booked the two bedroom apartment. It was very spacious and clean. Unfortunately they are building next door and we were on that side. The noise from the building site went on all night some nights. We managed to sleep through most of it! Da nang is noisy anyway and the sounds of traffic horns goes on all night mixed in with the construction I found it lulling! We ate in the top bar and the restaurant and both were good. All in all it was a good place to stay. I would…
Date of stay: December 2018
Xin chao Jane-ChrisBScotland, Thank you for taking the time to post your comments on TripAdvisor after your recent staying with us. We are delighted to read you enjoyed our room and the our restaurant. We have noted with great concern your comments and the low rating regarding your experience and we apologize most sincerely that you did not have an enjoyable stay with us. As you may have seen on numerous reviews, this is very unusual for us to receive such feedback and even more so concerning thereby. Whilst you have highlighted your experience, we will continue to work hard to ensure all our guests are made to feel welcome. We would be very grateful for the opportunity to welcome you back to our hotel in the future and we do hope you will give us another chance to provide you with the quality of service. Yours sincerely,
