yinanson wrote a review Dec 2018
Hong Kong, China12 contributions7 helpful votes
Room is spacious but far too noise to rest!
In general my overall impression of this hotel is good. I stayed at this hotel for several nights. I like that the room is quite spacious and the price is quite reasonable at X-Mas holiday. For the breakfast, the Pho provided is in so far the best I have tried in Da Nang and every time I had my breakfast I had 2-3 bowls of Pho. I planned to rate at least 5 for this hotel, but a 3 is given instead because of the following three reasons: 1. In some nights after taking a 10-mins shower by my partner and I, there’s no more hot water! 2. The speed of WIFI is very slow from 8-11pm and I can barely get access to the internet! 3. The most critical reason for giving a 3-star review - IF YOU WOULD LIKE TO TAKE A REST BEFORE 10pm, never stay at this hotel BECAUSE there’s a night club…
Responded Dec 28, 2018
Xin chao yinanson, Firstly I would like to thank you for taking the time to advise of your stay at A La Carte Danang Beach. It is only through feedback such as yours that we are able to maintain and indeed, where necessary, improve upon the service that we provide to our value guests. I was very disappointed to read of your experience during your stay with us. Whilst an apology will regrettably not after the outcome of your occasion, I do extend it with all sincerity. I certainly empathize regarding the points you mention in your review, especially the noise you experience of the CLUB next to our hotel, however it shut down by 10pm by Vietnamese Law daily anyway.
Ricky Celkos wrote a review Dec 2018
2 contributions
Just wonderful!!
What a lovely hotel and perfect services ! That was our 2nd stay at A La Carte and we had never thought about staying anywhere else in Da Nang. We loved everything about our stay. The hotel had a good position that was close to entertaining areas, restaurants. Clean and spacious with beautiful ocean view. Good food, excellent buffet, all the staffs were wonderful and did a good job, nothing is too much for them. We enjoyed some massages in the spa and found it so relaxing. I wish I could stay there longer and experience much more! Looking forward to staying with you again in 2019.
Date of stay: November 2018
Xin chào RickyCelkos, Thank you for taking the time to write a review. I am pleased to learn you were generally happy with your stay especially our service. Your feedback serves as great motivation for us all. The team and I appreciate your feedback and we all look forward to your return in the not too distant future. Sincerely, The A La Carte management team.
