Samrat D wrote a review Dec 2018
Xóm Da Me, Vietnam6 contributions7 helpful votes
Pros n Cons
PROS - very spacious rooms , -quiet on the floors , lifts are fast even they have 23 floors . -Clean and welcoming front desk . -90% Cheerful staffs CONS - Massage expensive than intentional standard compared to a 5 star -WiFi - Very slow ! Takes too long to download even a 30 sec video from any media ... so Better get a data package if you are selecting this hotel -Breakfast- Bad experience, the egg & noodle making guy have a bad behaviour of staring at women .. my wife had to ask me accompanying her for the 2nd round she went to the counter . Even I could feel the unpleasantness right up and all along when standing there !
Response from ALC S, Manager at A La Carte Da Nang Beach
Responded Dec 13, 2018
Xin chao Samrat D, First, I want to thank you for your feedback for a la carte. While I wish, you had a better experience, it is feedback like this that we learn from and use to improve. We work hard to deliver an exceptional guest experience, and it’s apparent in this case, we fell short. At the time, you were staying with us, the whole city wifi was out of service for routine maintenance. For the inconvenience, it caused, I am sorry. And for the bad experience you had with our staff, we have assured that the matter has been discussed with relative department to ensure it will not happen in the future.The safety of our guests is a priority and such service is an unavoidable necessity that should have been better explained. If you give us a chance to earn back your trust, I can assure you that your breakfast will be on time and your towels will be plentiful. I would be happy to make your reservation personally and and see to it that you enjoy the experience that so many of our guests have grown so fond of. Yours sincerely,
